##Special Report | Can the food and beverage industry, shut down by the outbreak, save itself by just taking out food?

Hey, guys

Function description, here is the "First Finance" magazine (predecessor "first finance weekly") readers club, we discover wonderful business value for you, also invited you to explore the bright business world.

"Who would have thought that during the Spring Festival, we would have all the supplies we needed, the year-end bonus for our employees would have been paid out, and the company's cash flow would have been low. "

By Betty Liu

Intern reporter | Tao Zidong

Editor | Wang Shanshan

The 2020 lobster season "is going to be a turnaround, " according to Ma's original vision. But the outbreak of COVID-19 has thrown everything into disarray.

Now, as the founder of Shanghai Red Lobster Shop "Huxiaopang" , Ma Ji can do nothing but "wait for the epidemic to pass" at home. By this time of year, he was already busy with shop maintenance, hiring and preparing for the lobster season after March.

After 16 years of painstaking management, "Shanghai Xiaopang" has opened 13 direct stores in Shanghai. Diners have a taste of lobster every year, and lobster has not been as popular as before in the past two years. Ma Ji, taking advantage of the low lobster season in winter, has just invested 10 million yuan in opening a new restaurant in Shanghai and another in Beijing to seek a transformation of dishes, unexpectedly, the sudden outbreak of the disease, so that the construction of the new store is stuck in there.

For now, the bigger crisis for Magee is how long the company's cash reserves can be kept out of business for.

Shanghai Xiaopang closed all its stores on the 25th day of the Lunar New Year (January 19) , with more than 500 employees taking time off to go home for the holiday. Now, with the exception of Ma Ji, who has returned to Shanghai on his own, the rest of the staff are stuck at home. Ma Ji did not expect "the epidemic will deteriorate so quickly. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Shanghai Xiao Pang closed all its stores on the 25th day of the Lunar New Year (January 19) and has yet to resume normal business.

13 directly operated stores, the Single Day's rent and labor cost is 100,000 yuan, the dining hall does not have the business zero income situation to last month, this "fixed expense" is more than 3 million yuan, not a penny less. "Sibei said it would last for three months, but small and medium-sized enterprises like ours may not last that long, " Ma told YiMagazine.

While the film Spring Festival stalls have all been canceled, the catering industry is hoping to make a big profit in the "Spring Festival stalls" this year, as well. On February 1, Jia Guolong, chairman of xibei catering, complained to the media that he expected to lose 700 million to 800 million yuan in revenue in the month around the Spring Festival due to the epidemic. More than 400 Xibeixiaomian villages in more than 60 cities across the country have basically suspended their canteen business, with only more than 100 takeaway businesses remaining.

Retail and catering companies across the country achieved sales of about 1,005 billion yuan, compared with 2019, from New Year's Eve to the sixth day of the first lunar month, according to a recent report entitled "analysis of the Impact of the epidemic on China's economy and Policy Recommendations" released by the Evergrande Research Institute, in the same period this year, retail sales of food and beverage are expected to be less than half of last year's total, just 500 billion yuan.

Business just shut down

At the end of 2019, the National Hot Pot Restaurant Chain, Da Long, also held a year-end summary meeting with high morale. The Chairman of the board, Liu Zhiru, made an appointment to issue year-end bonuses to employees, at the annual meeting, I outlined a beautiful blueprint for 2020——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————

"The staff were very happy that night. Next, we will prepare for the Spring Festival Dinner Rush. But we didn't expect the whole Spring Festival to turn into this, " Liu told YiMagazine.

Leaving behind a bleak Spring Festival business, the point at which the epidemic occurred is the most wronged place in Liu Ji, "Who would have thought that during the Spring Festival, we would have all the supplies we needed, the year-end bonuses for our employees would have been paid out, and the company's cash flow would have been low. "

Founded in Chengdu, Da Long Yi currently in the country has nearly 300 stores, including sub-brands including 11 direct shop. On January 25, the Chengdu Market Supervision Bureau and the Commerce Bureau jointly issued a notice, in order to prevent and control the spread of the epidemic, the city is prohibited from holding group catering activities, the lifting of the ban will be announced separately. On January 26, all of Magnosaurus's directly operated stores were closed, and subsequently, franchise stores across the country were closed.

Last year, the first day of the first month to the ninth day of the Big Yilong 11 directly operated outlets turnover as high as 4.99 million yuan, and this year only 320,000 yuan, down more than 90% . Dalong Yi needs 1.1 million yuan a month for rent and property management fees, 200,000 yuan for tax, 600,000 yuan for energy costs for normal operation, and 1.7 million yuan for the salary cost of more than 360 employees. "Fortunately, we have set aside more than 10 million yuan to build the factory, plus the one million yuan cash reserve left from normal operation before, which will probably last for a period of time, " Liu predicted, including the impact on the franchise stores and the suspension of supply chain operations, there is a good chance that the company will have no revenue through the first half of this year.

Da Long Yimen store, staff before starting to measure body temperature.

In Shanghai has slowly developed 19 directly-owned stores Sichuan night snack brand red cuisine, "the fifth day of the Lunar New Year to resume business, " the plan is all gone. On the fifth day of the Lunar New Year, Zhao Rong, director of red cuisine, went to the store to greet the employees. All the chairs in the store were covered on the tables with their backs facing up.

A growing number of returning shop assistants have told the company that local villages have closed roads and may not be able to return to their stores on the fifth day as planned. "The first reaction was, what if the staff can't go back to work? And in order to keep the food fresh, the food market has to deliver to the stores every day under normal circumstances. Whether the normal supply can be restored after years is also an issue. " Until the fifth day of the eighth Lunar Month, red's can only first opened 14 stores take-out business, strengthen security measures, waiting for the resumption of canteen.

It's time to save yourself

Liu recalled that he held as many as five meetings a day, starting with the closure of the canteen business. "A lot of businesses that used to be ignored are now being managed, including staff scheduling, takeout and pacifying franchisees. "

These two days, Liu Ji has negotiated with a landlord, who is willing to reduce the rent for one and a half months. Others are still in communication. "If you can't talk about a waiver, the worst thing you can do is just close two inefficient stores because the rent is so expensive. "

Rent-free, for short-term zero-income catering enterprises is one of the most direct assistance. On January 26, Poly Property commercial announced that it would waive the rents of its 22 shopping centres for six days during the first six days of the Lunar New Year. On January 28, the Wanda Commercial Management Group announced that it would implement a rent and property fee waiver policy for all merchants in Wanda Plaza, with a rent reduction estimated at 3 billion to 4 billion yuan. Longhu group also announced a two-month rent reduction for its stores.

Personnel Deployment, Dalong at this stage only retain 64 employees, responsible for three takeaway site production and distribution, the use of rotation system. To save money, Dalong uses a pro rata payment method. Under the principle that monthly staff costs accounted for only half of the day-to-day operating costs during the outbreak, employees were paid only a portion of their salaries at the moment and would be compensated if business returned to normal. Among them, employees who rest at home will be paid 1,200 yuan per month according to the minimum guaranteed income in Chengdu, 60% of the salary due to employees above the director level, 90% of the salary due to the first-line employees, and all board members without pay.

"take-out is the only increment I can think of. " Liu Ji revealed that three direct-operated stores with good business started to engage in take-out in 2016. During the first 10 days of this year, take-out revenue was 1.81 million yuan, up 547 percent year-on-year. In order to pull the sales volume of take-away business, Dalong Yi mobilizes all the staff to promote hot pot take-away products through the circle of friends. If the order volume is large, Da Long Yi will continue to increase the delivery business site.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Stores can not operate normally, take-out business is the only increment of many catering enterprises.

Red Cuisine formed an emergency team during the Spring Festival. The purchase cycle of materials was originally direct daily delivery, and was limited by the shortage of local specialties in the country of origin, which led to serious loss of food materials and shortage of goods, the daily business hours have been shortened by two hours, and take-out dishes are adjusted whenever there is a shortage of goods. The former canteen staff were temporarily transferred to clean the kitchen or pack takeout food to expand the number of delivery staff. However, Zhao Rong, brand director of red cuisine, still believes that if the dining hall part of the catering enterprises can not open for a long time, only rely on takeout, it will inevitably form an unhealthy financial model. Moreover at present many small area implements the blockade policy, reduced the consumer to order the take-out the convenience, has also caused the not small influence to the take-out order quantity.

Liu Ji introduced that not all restaurants can switch to take-away food in a short time, "The running process takes about half a month, and the delivery equipment and packaging costs about 100,000 yuan. If you don't run the order first, you'll die faster. "

Can't wait for the Dawn

On January 31, Ali local life released a letter to all business partners, exempting all word of mouth businesses nationwide from commission until February 29,2020. The annual fee was extended to launch the "fast delivery online service" , businesses on the day of the application to open takeout business and other policy support.

But catering companies are hoping ele.me and Meituan can implement a phased reduction in commissions in more cities than Wuhan to help companies that currently only carry out takeout to tide over the epidemic.

Poke Lab, an online celebrity restaurant in Shanghai that sells Hawaiian seafood, announced its "zero-yuan transfer" through its wechat account on Feb. 3. Poke Lab was founded in 2017 by two girls who had quit apple to start their own business. They have experienced the Apple Store side of the customer experience, starting with a 14-square-metre shop in Piazza del Popolo, where they had a vision for the start-up and quickly established a brand reputation through real materials.

With so much imported raw food, the cost per unit has determined that Poke Lab's business model is a niche Internet restaurant. By the end of 2019, it had just two stores. At the best of times, the stores'monthly revenue was 300,000 yuan and gross profit margin was 70 percent, according to founder Liu Jia. But catering has always been a cash-flow business, for small and micro-scale brands, it is necessary to be careful about spending, and an epidemic can easily destroy its fragile cash flow capacity.

The outbreak is a major test for small and micro-scale restaurant brands.

Poke Lab, which has accumulated more than 7,000 members, has traditionally been in high demand since the end of the Lunar New Year holiday. But this year's 20-day restaurant "zero revenue" has left Poke Lab unable to pay for the upcoming store rentals of December and January. In addition, some of the shop assistants are from Wenzhou, and some of them are back to Hubei for the New Year. It is doubtful whether they can resume work in time.

Although takeout once made up a third of Poke Lab's take out revenue, Liu Jia's assessment was that it would be impractical to switch to just takeout. First of all, it's impossible to close a store on a long term lease, and second of all, takeout platforms charge a high percentage of commission, such as a 20% cut on Poke Lab orders, plus the cost of online traffic, "If you just do take-out, you don't have a lot of surplus every month, and you'll lose money if you don't do it right. "

"There are a lot of restaurateurs in Shanghai who are watching the world go by, " Liu Jia told Yimagazine, a financial magazine, after discussions with several partners and deciding to abandon the venture, put Forward 0 yuan transfer is to be able to continue to retain the restaurant brand as far as possible. The immediate cost of the offer, however, is the overdue rent.

"We didn't want to just close the store, because from my point of view it was emotional, and I thought it was the best thing if it survived, and a lot of customers loved our product, " Liu Jia said, she hopes to entrust the Poke Lab to a man with a lot of money who will be able to bring the restaurant back to life.
